1. Run `bosh stop SELECTED-VM` for each Cloud Controller VM. Stopped VMs have their state listed as `failing`.
<pre class='terminal'>
    $ bosh stop cloud\_controller-partition-bd784aa8b15f/0
    Acting as user 'director'...
    <br>
    You are about to stop cloud\_controller-partition-bd784aa8b15f/0
    <br>
    Detecting deployment changes
    \-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-
    Stop cloud\_controller-partition-bd784aa8b15f/0? (type 'yes' to continue)

</pre>
You do not need to stop the Cloud Controller worker VMs.